sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K592027
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The promoter T5-lac (<partinfo>BBa_K592008</partinfo>) for testing its promoter strength coupled with BFP (<partinfo>BBa_K592100</partinfo>). This construct should be cloned into pSB3K3 plasmid to measure the BFP output and thereby determine the promoter strength. Theoretically, the promoter should be well-repressed in LacIq strain but inducible by high concentrations of IPTG.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lei Sun
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The information of <partinfo>BBa_K592008</partinfo> and <partinfo>BBa_K592100</partinfo> can be found in the registry. T5-lac promoter is a fusion promoter with parts from T5 phage.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was assembled into pSB3K3 for testing, and later cloned into pSB1C3 for submission.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: PT5lac
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: T5-lac promoter is a hybrid promoter made from the phage T5 early promoter and lac-operon. It contains three LacI binding sites and remains repressed in LacIq strains where LacI is expressed in high levels. It is inducible by IPTG, and recognizable by E.coli RNA polymerase. Compared to the T7 promoters, T5-lac promoter doesn't require the co-expression of phage polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Erik Lundin
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The most common DH5alpha and TOP10 used in assembly are not LacI-constitutive (LacIq) strains. Thus, any ORF placed downstream to this promoter will be massively transcribed. Therefore, it's recommended to employ low-copy number plasmids or even LacIq strains when adding genes to this promoter.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part codes for the bright blue fluorescent protein mTagBFP. mTagBFP is a monomeric protein with a narrow fluorescence emission spectrum with a maximum at 456 nm. It has a tyrosine-based chromophore, giving it substantially higher brightness, faster chromophore maturation and higher pH stability than blue fluorescent proteins with a histidine in the chromophore. Subach et. al. started with a red fluorescent protein (TagRed) and converted it to a bright blue monomeric protein. See the article listed in source. The sequence has been codon optimized for expression in E coli by DNA 2.0.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Erik Gullberg
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Subach, O. M., I. S. Gundorov, et al. (2008). "Conversion of red fluorescent protein into a bright blue probe." Chem Biol 15(10): 1116-24.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The sequence has been codon optimized for expression in E coli by DNA 2.0.
